creditline: Gift of Frederick J. Whitehead from the collection compiled by his father Cornelius Whitehead at the Pacific Print Works of Lawrence, Massachusetts
description: Small notebook with handwritten formulas for dyestuffs to be used for printing textiles.  There are 253 samples of printed cotton fabrics in various patterns: geometric, flowers, stripes, checks.
